article.headline: North Texas 78, Indiana St. 69
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Collin Dennis scored a career-high 22 points and Quincy Williams had 14 points and 19 rebounds to lead North Texas past Indiana State 78-69 Saturday. Dennis scored five points in a 9-0 run that put North Texas (3-0) ahead 56-38 early in the second half. Indiana State (1-2) got within 74-67 in the final minute, but the Mean Green's Dez Willingham iced the game with four straight free throws. Marico Stinson scored 15 points and Gabe Moore added 12 for the Sycamores. Dennis was 11-of-13 from the foul line and hit three 3-pointers. Josh White added 11 points for North Texas.
